page.title: 14ECOLOGY
page.content: ALTHOUGH THIS AREA IS DENSELY POPULATED AND HEAVILY BUILT UP,THERE IS A GREAT DEAL OF NATURE EVIDENT IN THE PARKS, OPEN SPACES,GRAVEYARDS AND GARDENS. ALL TYPES OF WILD FLOWERS,TREES, GRASSES,WILD BIRDS AND INSECTS ARE SEEN. GREY SQUIRRELS,FOXES AND HEDGEHOGS ARE FREQUENT INHABITANTS OF THE SUBURBAN GARDEN. A VERY COMMON GARDEN INSECT IS THE STAG BEETLE AND ONE OF THE MOST COMMON TREES IN THE AREA IS THE ENGLISH OAK. APART FROM THE COMMON SPARROW,THE MOST FREQUENTLY SEEN BIRD IS THE STARLING.
